March 27th 35
Dearest Enid:
Your good letter to Daddy and me was a joy and I am so glad you wrote it. 
Of course you want to be in the country - and I hope you will be West - but Oh don't be in a hurry to get married - you should try to put that out of your mind as it will hap pen soon enough any way! 
It seems my chances are fine once more with Mr Good's bust. Mr Leonard who 
gave me the order was here form Kansas City - and be talked Mr Good into reconsidering the propo-sition. So Mr. Good told Mr Leonard, if he pro-mised to box the bust <del>it</del> when done, and not show it to anyone till after his death he woudl consent to hav eit done and have Mr Nei-hardt take the necessary pictures when he returns from his next little trip - so that is how it stands now! Is this not most 

